#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:7
msgid ""
"We, the management of Flying Circus Internet Operations, decided to "
"establish an Information Security Management System (ISMS) according to "
"the international standard ISO/IEC 27001."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:9
msgid ""
"This ISMS policy represents the basis of the organisational ISMS, "
"defining the elementary goals, strategies, and the framework of the ISMS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:12
msgid "Objective"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:14
msgid ""
"We mainly operate in the area of the managed hosting of critical business"
" applications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:16
msgid "Information security is crucial for our economic viability. The ISMS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:18
msgid ""
"ensures information is secured in relation to the required protection "
"level"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:19
msgid "helps us to avoid violating information security,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:20
msgid "and thus protect our customers and ourselves from economical damage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:22
msgid ""
"The targeted security level represents the baseline for a risk-oriented "
"and economically appropriate procedure. Internal requirements (company "
"rules or standards) and external requirements (customer, legal, or "
"regulatory obligations) are duly considered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:24
msgid ""
"To reach the objective and to take on overall responsibility the "
"management of FCIO establishes an ISMS, an information security "
"organisation, and ensures sufficient resources."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:26
msgid ""
"This ISMS policy defines the management’s mandate towards the information"
" security organisation to plan, implement, control, and continually "
"improve a risk-based ISMS under due consideration of internal and "
"external requirements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:29
msgid "Goals and Principles of Information Security"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:31
msgid ""
"Information security at FCIO plays a significant role to accomplish the "
"business objectives. There must be appropriate safeguards to secure the "
"confidentiality, integrity, authenticity, and availability of "
"information. This will help us to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:33
msgid "ensure safety of operation,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:34
msgid "avoid unacceptable economical damage to us and our customers,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:35
msgid "comply with legal provisions, regulatory requirements, and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:36
msgid "comply with unit specific policies, business directives and procedures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:38
msgid "This leads to the following goals regarding information security:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:40
msgid ""
"Ensure that information security is managed at an adequate level of "
"maturity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:41
msgid ""
"Ensure that all significant risks are identified, evaluated, and reduced "
"to an acceptable level – taking into account the entire value chain and "
"life cycle of information and its associated resources."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:42
msgid ""
"Engage staff and ensure that they follow specific policies, business "
"directives, and procedures for information security."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:43
msgid ""
"Ensure that service providers and partner companies follow relevant "
"requirements out of specified policies, business directives, and "
"procedures for information security."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:45
msgid ""
"The commitment to accomplish the above goals is to be carried forward "
"into practice through the following key points:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:47
msgid ""
"The management assumes personal responsibility for information security "
"and demonstrates active leadership."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:48
msgid "We establish an ISMS which complies to ISO/IEC 27001."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:49
msgid ""
"There is open, transparent exchange with customers, partner companies, "
"and service providers regarding information security."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:50
msgid ""
"Staff is appropriately educated, trained, and informed to follow defined "
"policies, business directives, and procedures for information security."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/policy.rst:51
msgid ""
"Trends, developments, upcoming threats in information security are "
"actively observed and assessed with regard to their relevance to us."
msgstr ""

